name: APT31 Stole and Used an Unknown Equation Group 0-Day
description:
These IOCs originate in A Check Point report analyzing “Jian”, the Chinese
(APT31 / Zirconium) exploit for CVE-2017-0005, which was reported initially by
Lockheed Martin’s Computer Incident Response Team. Surprisingly, Check Point
found out that this APT31 exploit is in fact a reconstructed version of an
Equation Group exploit called “EpMe”. This means that an Equation Group
exploit was eventually used by a Chinese-affiliated group, probably against
American targets. And Check Point shows that this happened before the Shadow
Brokers' leak in 2017. Note 1: Equation Group is the name given by the CTI
community to the Tailored Access Operations (TAO) unit of the NSA.
DanderSpritz is an Equation Group's modular post-exploitation framework that
contains dozens of different interdependent modules. Note 2: This isn’t the
first documented case of a Chinese APT using an Equation Group 0-Day. The
first was when APT3 used their own version of EternalSynergy (called
UPSynergy), after acquiring the Equation Group EternalRomance exploit.
However, in the UPSynergy case, the consensus among the security researchers
community was that the Chinese exploit was reconstructed from captured network
traffic.
